abstract: The 2020 Democrats headed West to campaign in two key states. “I don’t think it matters what happens in New Hampshire or Iowa, which are not representative of the country,” Harry Reid said.
snippet: The 2020 Democrats headed West to campaign in two key states. “I don’t think it matters what happens in New Hampshire or Iowa, which are not representative of the country,” Harry Reid said.
lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — Want to understand Iowa’s outsize role in selecting the Democratic presidential nominee? Just come to the West, where anyone in Nevada or California will tell you: We are the voters presidential candidates should be paying more attention to.

abstract: The campaign said the photo, displayed on a webpage touting the candidate’s anti-racism plan, was posted by a contractor who didn’t know where it was taken.
snippet: The campaign said the photo, displayed on a webpage touting the candidate’s anti-racism plan, was posted by a contractor who didn’t know where it was taken.
lead_paragraph: Pete Buttigieg’s presidential campaign, struggling to build support among black voters, removed from its website a photo of a Kenyan woman that was used earlier this year to illustrate his plan to dismantle racism in the United States.

abstract: The Foreign Ministry said an article based on government records had smeared China’s war on terrorism, but did not dispute the documents’ authenticity.
snippet: The Foreign Ministry said an article based on government records had smeared China’s war on terrorism, but did not dispute the documents’ authenticity.
lead_paragraph: BEIJING — The Chinese government on Monday portrayed the country’s crackdown in the western region of Xinjiang as a great success against terrorism, trying to counter renewed international criticism prompted by a New York Times article detailing the internal deliberations that led to the mass detention of Muslims in re-education camps and prisons.

abstract: A cultural suspicion about big cities seems to be part of the problem, but that attitude might be changing.
snippet: A cultural suspicion about big cities seems to be part of the problem, but that attitude might be changing.
lead_paragraph: In the history of American politics, one fact distills the nation’s enduring suspicion of cities: Voters have never elected a sitting mayor to the presidency.

headline_print_headline: Why Mayors Don’t Grow Up to Be President

abstract: New entrants into the race. A nod from Barack Obama. Centrist victories in governor’s contests. Moderates sense a favorable shift.
snippet: New entrants into the race. A nod from Barack Obama. Centrist victories in governor’s contests. Moderates sense a favorable shift.
lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — After spending months in anxious passivity, staking their hopes on Joseph R. Biden Jr. and little else, moderate Democrats appear suddenly determined to fight for control of their party in the 2020 elections.

abstract: Ahead of a possible Democratic run for president, the former mayor of New York City reversed himself before an important party constituency: black voters.
snippet: Ahead of a possible Democratic run for president, the former mayor of New York City reversed himself before an important party constituency: black voters.
lead_paragraph: Ahead of a potential Democratic presidential run, former Mayor Michael R. Bloomberg of New York on Sunday reversed his longstanding support of the aggressive “stop-and-frisk” policing strategy that he pursued for a decade and that led to the disproportionate stopping of black and Latino people across the city.
